Five drivers were arrested for various road traffic violations. Traffic fines worth more than R310,000 have also been issued. CAPE TOWN - Thirty-eight drunk drivers have been arrested in the Western Cape since the start of the weekend. Five drivers were arrested for various road traffic violations. Traffic fines worth more than R310,000 have also been issued. Provincial Traffic Chief Kenny Africa says no fatalities have been reported. “The highest reading recorded was a reading of 1.48mg/1,000ml. And that was six times over the legal limit in the Worcester. In Swellendam, we also arrested a driver for assault and in Somerset West, two drivers were arrested for being in possession of false documentation.”